 Establish and adhere to covid sanitization protocols in 2020 and ensured staff education and compliance.

PRIVATE CHEF

College Chefs, LLC Des Moines, Iowa / 2012 2015

 

 Manage the daily culinary operations in a sorority house with 65 girls in house and up to 200 for chapter dinner.

 Plan, prepare and execute new menus on a weekly basis keeping dietary restrictions in mind.

 Prepare and serve 10 meals per week. Desserts are made daily. College Chefs is based on the principal that fresh is best. All of our cooking is done from scratch and no premade products are purchased.

 Maintain weekly budget amounts being extra careful not to exceed the allotted amount per house.

 Always keep kitchen clean and organized, even during times of peak business. It is an open kitchen and its very important to maintain cleanliness.

 Maintain stock of coffee/ Breakfast bar.

 Provide pictures to College Chefs of the food that is produced.

 

 

Executive Sous Chef

Echo Valley Country Club, Norwalk, IA 2010-2012

 

 Assists the Executive Chef in the daily operations of the kitchen, including menu development, inventory and purchasing of supplies, and cost control.

 Oversees the activities of the kitchen staff and monitors food production and presentation.

 Understanding of federal, state, and local food sanitation regulations.

 Coordinates and participates in the activities of hiring, training, and managing personnel in the kitchen. Familiar with a variety of the field''s concepts, practices, and procedures.

 Rely on extensive experience and judgment to plan and accomplish goals.

 Responsible for placing/receiving all orders, writing the schedule, completing all prep within a day.

 Lead cooks on daily basis, which includes line cooking and banquet production.

 Typically report to the General Manager and/or Owner.

 Recruit and hire staff, including cooks and other kitchen workers; Supervise and coordinate activities of cooks and workers engaged in food preparation; Demonstrate new cooking techniques and equipment to staff; Monitor sanitation practices to ensure that employees follow standards and regulations.

  Meet with sales representatives in order to negotiate prices and order supplies; Inspect supplies, equipment, and work areas to ensure conformance to established standards; Record production and operational data as necessary.

 Determine how food should be presented, and create decorative food displays; Analyze recipes to assign prices to menu items, based on food, labor, and overhead costs; Meet with customers to discuss menus for special occasions such as parties, and banquets; Prepare and cook foods of all types, either on a regular basis or for special guests or functions

 

Kitchen Supervisor

Marriott, West Des Moines, IA 2008-2010

 

 Supervise and coordinate activities of food preparation; kitchen, pantry, and storeroom personnel, as well as purchases and kitchen supplies.

 Plan and participate in planning menus, preparing and apportioning foods, and utilizing food surpluses and leftovers.

 Specify number of servings to be made from any vegetable, meat, beverage, and dessert to control portion costs.

 Lead banquet service acting as the Banquet Chef. Most of the business was within the catering realm. Led the team to execute banquets successfully.

 

Line Chef/Banquet Chef

Troon Golf, Phoenix AZ 2006-2007; St. James, NC 2007-2008

 

 Responsibilities of a Line Chef; the daily preparation of food items in the pantry, fry stations, broiler, grill, saut or other areas of the kitchen.

 Promoted and transferred within the company to Banquet Chef.

 Responsibilities as the Banquet Chef; Design and execute meal services for multiple guests. Understand the dynamics of a high-volume kitchen. Execute the service portion of a function with precision and efficiency.
